  <title>Manage mailing lists</title>

  <para>NovaForge allows the project manager to create and manage mailing lists.
  In this section we will see how to add and manage a mailing list.
   To do this, simply select the menu <emphasis role="bold">My project space</emphasis>
   and then select the application : <emphasis role="bold">Your mailing lists</emphasis>. </para>

  <figure>
    <title>Administration of mailing lists</title>

    <mediaobject>
      <imageobject>
        <imagedata align="center"
                   fileref="04-04-01-ManageMailingListMenu.png"
                   width="200.px"/>
      </imageobject>
    </mediaobject>
  </figure>

  <para>The application "Your Mailing Lists" is displayed.</para>

  <figure>
    <title>Menu of project mailing lists</title>

    <mediaobject>
      <imageobject>
        <imagedata align="center"
                   fileref="04-04-02-DisplayMailingListMenu.png"
                   width="500.px" heigh="200.px"/>
      </imageobject>
    </mediaobject>
  </figure>

  <para>The private mailing list <emphasis role="bold">projectname-team@hostname</emphasis> is created by default for the project. It contains all project users. It can not be deleted or modified</para>

  <sect2>
    <title>Create a mailing list</title>

    <para>The project administrator can create a mailing list by activating the button
    <emphasis role="bold">Create a mailing list</emphasis> and filling in the following fields :</para>

    <figure>
      <title>Mailing List field</title>

      <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata align="center" fileref="04-04-03-CreationMailingList.png" width="300.px"/>
        </imageobject>
      </mediaobject>
    </figure>

    <para>A mailing list has two types : private (visible only to the members of this list) or public (visible to all members of the project, they can subscribe / unsubscribe to this list).
    </para>
    </sect2>
   <sect2>
    <title>Actions on a mailing list</title>
   
    <para>The project administrator can on the "ACTION" column below <emphasis role="bold">: View mailing list informations, Subscribe/Unsubscribe to the mailing list, Manage subscribers and Delete mailing list</emphasis>.</para>
    <para>The project user subscribed to a public list can only <emphasis role="bold">: View mailing list informations, Subscribe/Unsubscribe to the mailing list</emphasis>.</para>
    <para>The project user subscribed to a private list can only <emphasis role="bold">: View mailing list informations, Unsubscribe to the mailing list</emphasis>.</para>
   <figure>
      <title>Actions</title>

      <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata align="center" fileref="04-04-04-ActionMailingList.png" width="500.px" heigh="200.px"/>
        </imageobject>
      </mediaobject>
    </figure>
  </sect2>

  <sect2>
    <title>Manage subscribers</title>

    <para>The action <emphasis role="bold">Manage subscribers</emphasis> in the "ACTION" column allows the project manager to add/remove emails of project and forge users also external emails.</para>

    <figure>
      <title>Manage subscribers window</title>

      <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata align="center" fileref="04-04-05-manageUserMailingList.png" width="500.px" heigh="200.px"/>
        </imageobject>
      </mediaobject>
    </figure>

    <para>The button <emphasis role="bold">Add a new subscriber</emphasis> opens a popup that displays four categories of email to subscribe.</para>
    <figure>
      <title>Type of email to subscribe</title>

      <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata align="center" fileref="04-04-06-popupeUserMailingList.png" width="300.px"/>
        </imageobject>
      </mediaobject>
    </figure>
    
    <para>A table displays the forge or project users to subscribe if the choice type is  <emphasis role="bold">Project Users</emphasis> or <emphasis role="bold">Forge Users</emphasis></para>
     <figure>
      <title>Subscribe projet/forge users</title>

      <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata align="center" fileref="04-04-06-01-popupeUserMailingListUsers.png" width="300.px"/>
        </imageobject>
      </mediaobject>
    </figure>
    <para>An input field will be displayed if the selection type is <emphasis role="bold">External Emails</emphasis></para>

    <figure>
      <title>Subscribe external emails</title>

      <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata align="center" fileref="04-04-06-02-popupeUserMailingListExterne.png" width="300.px"/>
        </imageobject>
      </mediaobject>
    </figure>
    
     <para>A table displays the available groups in the project (with hertited groups from forge project) if the selection type is <emphasis role="bold">Groups</emphasis></para>

    <figure>
      <title>Subscribe groups</title>

      <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata align="center" fileref="04-04-06-03-popupeUserMailingListGroups.png" width="300.px"/>
        </imageobject>
      </mediaobject>
    </figure>
    
  </sect2>
  
 
</sect1>